3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper introduces new families of zero-difference balanced functions and investigates their properties, which are topics in discrete mathematics. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses the properties of APN functions, which are important in cryptography and security. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the construction of strongly regular graphs using partial difference sets, which is a topic in numerical analysis.
